subSubSection.paragraph:
Colour
. The carapace of fresh 

P. edwardsii

is brown to reddish-brown, with many specimens having the posterior part of the carapace slightly to much darker in colour (
Fig. 56A, C
), with the outer surface of the chela red, the colour extending to at least the middle of both fingers, with the distal half white (
Fig. 56B, D, E
) (see also 
Ng & Schubart, 2017
).
